Hard to tell without more of your code. How is self.SlickGrid defined? If it’s an Observable you need to access it like a function using **()**:
 

    self.SlickGrid().focus();
    self.SlickGrid().resetActiveCell();
    self.SlickGrid().setSelectedRows([0]);
    self.SlickGrid().onClick.notify({ row: 0 });

This is because ko.observable objects are actually functions. In this case you want the value so you have to call the function with no parameters.

More info about ko.observable here: https://knockoutjs.com/documentation/observables.html

